	<div class="posts">
    <a name="113995119180960237"></a>
    
     <h2><font color="#000080"><!-- 2004-09-02 -->
	 
	 brrreeeport
	 </font>
     </h2>
    

	<p>
    <div style="clear:both;"></div><p><a href="http://scobleizer.wordpress.com/2006/02/14/brrreeeport-report/">Scoble&rsquo;s Brrreeeport Report</a>.&nbsp; Well, I need some kinda comic relief.&nbsp; I have run out of ideas for getting technorati tags actually working on my blog.&nbsp; Click on any of them in preceding articles and notice how those articles, sometimes those tags, have no presence in the technoratisphere.&nbsp; I&rsquo;m told the way to get attention on this sort of thing is to mention the Dave guy.&nbsp; OK, we&rsquo;ll try that too.</p><p align="center">{tags: <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/brrreeeport" rel="tag">brrreeeport</a> </strong><a href="http://technorati.com/tag/technorati" rel="tag">technorati</a> <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/Dave+Sifry" rel="tag">Dave Sifry</a> <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/orcmid" rel="tag">orcmid</a>}</p><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom: 0.25em;"></div>
